Hotel Solipcyst

"Nothing but your mind may exist, after all. Once the idea has taken root, it is quite
impossible to dislodge the parasitic solipcyst."

- konsole with certain config
- recordmydesktop --full-shots --on-the-fly-encoding --v_bitrate 2000000 --no-sound -x 10 --width 1000 -y 25 --height 690 --no-cursor

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"Some choices are illusions"
+ 1.1 pan over tree

"Most lead you to more choices"
+ 1.2 pan over ferris wheel

"But one... will haunt you forever."
+ 1.3 pan up clocktower and stop

"Although you can never change your past"
+ 1.4 keyboard slowly spelling SUICIDE or DEATH

"You could always just... forget it." (drum BOOM)
+ 1.4 backspace key (blit 0 and 1 to flash)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"criminal on the run from thought, down slips the sun: you ought"
+ 2.1 fleeing red river towards hotel
      spotlights chasing the camera

"to check into your mind's hotel -- the appearance certainly does not sell --"
+2.1 spotlights going crazy, settle on the hotel

"but the registration desk has a bell to ding, attached to a string"
+ 2.2 lobby, lit

"of vivid consequence; since the rates are flat, bring in the troupes that"
+ 2.3 horde following you through self floor

"keep you company in your rooms; though the concierge looms"
+ 2.3 a room

"in shadows of a different lobby, this staff has the hobby"
+ 2.4 atrium, spotlights tracing

"of thundering through the halls to pounce upon the walls"
+ 2.5 vending/laundry hallway, black ominous staff

"of an elevator always going down to pursue an abstract noun"
+ 2.6 elevator

"lost in a different basement altogether, where dust too is the forecast of weather"
+ 2.7 overworld/staircase chamber, spotlight or just lit pan?

"since the shadows dress like a maid, no guests there stayed"
+ 2.8 pool, spotlight?

"your mind's hotel became a vacant place where the living began to race,"
+ 2.9 atrium or somewhere pouring with guests

"by moving brooms without the touch, for the dead, while you feverishly slept in bed"
+ 3.1 kitchen, a stove catching fire

"the skeleton roomkey clutched in a hand that no door would touch"
+ 3.2 lock & key suite

"where drinks are mixed for the sake of an aging bartender to make"
+ 3.3 RANDOM CODE! ???

"just one more vivid potion for the tourist, trapped in a motion"
+ 3.4 giftshop

"not entirely unlike your own, criminal."
+ 3.5 finish the continuous loop, leaving the hotel

